    searchSampleType

    searchSampleType.Rd

    search for BRENDA tissue name updated 02/2024

    searchSampleType(x, file = BRENDA, contain_all = TRUE)

    Arguments

    x

    A string or character vector to search for. Multiple search terms are separated by space.

    file

    The BRENDA data frame, has columns ID and Name.

    contain_all

    if TRUE, will only return the results contain all search terms. if FALSE, will return results contain any of the given pattern.

    Value

    matrix including search result

    Examples

    # search for results that contain all of "HEK" "293" and "T":
searchSampleType("HEK 293 T", contain_all = TRUE)
#>               ID                      Name
#> 2180 BTO:0002181             HEK-293T cell
#> 3346 BTO:0003347    HEK-293 Tet-On 3G cell
#> 5021 BTO:0005025         HEK-293-TrkB cell
#> 5025 BTO:0005029            HEK-293FT cell
#> 5544 BTO:0005548            HEK-293ET cell
#> 6318 BTO:0006322 Jump-In-T-REx HEK293 cell
#> 6324 BTO:0006328          HEK-293T/17 cell
#> 6509 BTO:0006513          HEK-293-AT1 cell
searchSampleType(c("HEK", "293", "T"), contain_all = TRUE)
#>               ID                      Name
#> 2180 BTO:0002181             HEK-293T cell
